int main ( int  argc,

)

Command Interpreter Node main function. Obtains speech from user and translate them into commands.

The command strings input by the user (typed in the terminal) are mapped to flags (integer values) and sent to the Command Logic Node.

If sentences are received, parsing the text is necessary, which must be done by calling the Speech Recognition Node (currently in development).
